cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the security concerns of deep learning systems and their vulnerability to adversarial attacks. It also proposes a defense technique to mitigate these attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization techniques, which suggest the possibility of it being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
